==English==

===Etymology===
From ''un-'', '''not''' + ''[[tenable]]'', '''holdable''', from Latin ''[[tenabilis]]'', from ''[[tenere]]'', '''hold''' + ''[[-abilis]]'', '''able'''

===Adjective===
'''untenable'''
# Not able to be held, as of an opinion or position; unholdable, [[indefensible]].
#: "The theory of cold fusion was '''untenable'''."

